    "start_blocks": "//Hey! I should comment my code!\n//This is a Proof of Concept level that shows a few things: drag-and-drop in App Lab, and Validation\n\n\n//This function is necessary for Validation to work in App Lab.\n//This thread has a bunch of historical knowledge: https://codedotorg.slack.com/archives/C1B3PNDL7/p1662482867134019\n//But essentially, the way validation works in App Lab is it relies on this running log of every command that runs in the program is kept. \n//You can access it in the developer console with Applab.currentExecutionLog\n//And then the validation works by comparing the log with an expected output.\n//So in this case, I'm making a success function and only calling it when I'm sure the level is complete\n//And then if you look at the \"Edit\" screen for this level in the validation section, you'll see a JSON object that essentially checks that this function was called at least 1 time\n//This makes the actual levelbuilding-validation pretty easy and could be re-used across different levels\n//And the actual validation logic can happen inside this starter code, which is what I do later in the program.\nfunction success() {\n  console.log(\"success\");\n}\n\n//A lot of the dragging logic came from this post on the forum: https://forum.code.org/t/is-there-a-way-to-code-a-drag-and-drop-behavior-on-an-image/13037/6\n//And then this project someone posted later with improvements on Baker's initial post: https://studio.code.org/projects/applab/g3Q6so46nK07lxfzyjF2waEkbpsJ6Rs5oFX3Meb18PE/view\n//One key detail is that in design mode, dragging works better on buttons than images. So all of the draggable elements are actually button design elements\n//The rest of the code is modeled after what the program above did, but abstracts some global variables to objects instead.\nvar dragObj = {\n  state: false,\n  curImg: null,\n  xOffset: 0,\n  yOffset: 0\n};\n\nfunction resetDragObj() {\n  dragObj.state = false;\n  dragObj.curImg = null;\n  dragObj.xOffset = 0;\n  dragObj.yOffset = 0;\n}\n\n//NOTE: in Design Mode, these are actually buttons due to an interaction with image types and dragging\nvar IMAGESARRAY = [\"imgA\", \"imgB\", \"imgC\", \"imgD\"];\n\n//This is just a clever way to generalize making onEvents for each draggable element.\nfor(var i = 0; i < IMAGESARRAY.length; i++) {\n  var curImg = IMAGESARRAY[i];\n  \n  //visual change to show is draggable\n  onEvent(curImg, \"mouseover\", function(e) {\n    //Because of how events calculate the ID, I need to use the event ID instead of the curImg variable\n    setProperty(e.targetId, \"border-width\", 2);\n  });\n  onEvent(curImg, \"mouseout\", function(e) {\n    setProperty(e.targetId, \"border-width\", 0);\n  });\n  \n  // start dragging currrent element\n  onEvent(curImg, \"mousedown\", function(e) {\n    console.log(e);\n    dragObj.state = true;\n    dragObj.curImg = e.targetId;\n    dragObj.xOffset = e.x - getProperty(e.targetId, \"x\");\n    dragObj.yOffset = e.y - getProperty(e.targetId, \"y\");\n  });\n}\n\nonEvent(\"screen1\", \"mouseup\", function() {\n  resetDragObj();\n});\n\nonEvent(\"screen1\", \"mousemove\", function(e){\n  if(dragObj.state == true){\n    //console.log(dragObj.curImg);\n    var newX = e.x - dragObj.xOffset;\n    var newY = e.y - dragObj.yOffset;\n    setPosition(dragObj.curImg, newX, newY, 100, 100);\n  }\n});\n\n//Checks if the center (x, y) of id1 is inside the bounding box of id2\nfunction checkInside(id1, id2) {\n  var id1Obj = {};\n  id1Obj.x = getProperty(id1, \"x\");\n  id1Obj.y = getProperty(id1, \"y\");\n  id1Obj.width = getProperty(id1, \"width\");\n  id1Obj.height = getProperty(id1, \"height\");\n  id1Obj.centerX = id1Obj.x + (id1Obj.width / 2);\n  id1Obj.centerY = id1Obj.y + (id1Obj.height / 2);\n  \n  var id2Obj = {};\n  id2Obj.x = getProperty(id2, \"x\");\n  id2Obj.y = getProperty(id2, \"y\");\n  id2Obj.width = getProperty(id2, \"width\");\n  id2Obj.height = getProperty(id2, \"height\");\n  id2Obj.centerX = id2Obj.x + (id2Obj.width / 2);\n  id2Obj.centerY = id2Obj.y + (id2Obj.height / 2);\n  \n  if((id1Obj.centerX > id2Obj.x && id1Obj.centerX < (id2Obj.x + id2Obj.width)) && (id1Obj.centerY > id2Obj.y && id1Obj.centerY < (id2Obj.y + id2Obj.height))) {\n    return true;\n  } else {\n    return false;\n  }\n}\n\n//This is my validation logic. When it's all true, I call \"success\", which is what the levelbuilder validation is looking for.\nonEvent(\"checkButton\", \"click\", function( ) {\n\tvar correct = 0;\n\tif(checkInside(\"imgA\", \"labelA\")) {\n\t  setProperty(\"labelA\", \"background-color\", \"green\");\n\t  correct += 1;\n\t}\n\tif(checkInside(\"imgB\", \"labelD\")) {\n\t  setProperty(\"labelD\", \"background-color\", \"green\");\n\t  correct += 1;\n\t}\n\tif(checkInside(\"imgC\", \"labelB\")) {\n\t  setProperty(\"labelB\", \"background-color\", \"green\");\n\t  correct += 1;\n\t}\n\tif(checkInside(\"imgD\", \"labelC\")) {\n\t  setProperty(\"labelC\", \"background-color\", \"green\");\n\t  correct += 1;\n\t}\n\tif(correct >= 4) {\n\t  success();\n\t}\n});",
    "start_html": "<div id=\"designModeViz\" class=\"appModern\" data-radium=\"true\" style=\"display: none; width: 600px; height: 450px;\"><div class=\"screen\" tabindex=\"1\" data-theme=\"default\" id=\"screen1\" style=\"display: block; height: 450px; width: 600px; left: 0px; top: 0px; position: absolute; z-index: 0; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\"><label style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 1; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 320px; border-style: solid; text-rendering: optimizespeed; color: rgb(77, 87, 95); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 2px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; padding: 2px 15px; width: 200px; height: 100px; position: absolute; left: 400px; font-size: 70px; text-align: center; top: 300px;\" id=\"labelD\">D</label><label style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 1; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 320px; border-style: solid; text-rendering: optimizespeed; color: rgb(77, 87, 95); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 2px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; padding: 2px 15px; width: 200px; height: 100px; position: absolute; left: 400px; top: 200px; font-size: 70px; text-align: center;\" id=\"labelC\">C</label><label style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 1; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 320px; border-style: solid; text-rendering: optimizespeed; color: rgb(77, 87, 95); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 2px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; padding: 2px 15px; width: 200px; height: 100px; position: absolute; left: 400px; top: 100px; font-size: 70px; text-align: center;\" id=\"labelB\">B</label><label style=\"margin: 0px; line-height: 1; overflow: hidden; overflow-wrap: break-word; max-width: 320px; border-style: solid; text-rendering: optimizespeed; color: rgb(77, 87, 95); background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 0px; border-width: 2px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; padding: 2px 15px; width: 200px; height: 100px; position: absolute; left: 400px; top: 0px; font-size: 70px; text-align: center;\" id=\"labelA\">A</label><button id=\"checkButton\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 35px; width: 150px; background-color: rgb(255, 164, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 4px; border-width: 1px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; position: absolute; left: 435px; top: 405px;\">Check Answers</button><button id=\"imgA\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 100px; width: 100px; background-color: rgba(255, 164, 0, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 4px; border-width: 0px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; position: absolute; left: -4.44089e-16px; top: -5px; background-size: contain; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat;\" data-canonical-image-url=\"icon://fa-smile-o\" data-image-type=\"icon\"></button><button id=\"imgB\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 100px; width: 100px; background-color: rgba(255, 164, 0, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 4px; border-width: 0px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; position: absolute; left: 0px; top: 100px; background-size: contain; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat;\" data-canonical-image-url=\"icon://fa-frown-o\" data-image-type=\"icon\"></button><button id=\"imgC\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 100px; width: 100px; background-color: rgba(255, 164, 0, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 4px; border-width: 0px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; position: absolute; left: 0px; background-size: contain; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat; top: 200px;\" data-canonical-image-url=\"icon://fa-meh-o\" data-image-type=\"icon\"></button><button id=\"imgD\" style=\"padding: 0px; margin: 0px; border-style: solid; height: 100px; width: 100px; background-color: rgba(255, 164, 0, 0); color: rgb(255, 255, 255); border-color: rgb(77, 87, 95); border-radius: 4px; border-width: 0px; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Gadget, sans-serif; font-size: 15px; position: absolute; left: 0px; background-size: contain; background-position: 50% 50%; background-repeat: no-repeat; top: 300px;\" data-canonical-image-url=\"icon://fa-star\" data-image-type=\"icon\"></button></div></div>",
    "long_instructions": "Click and drag each of the icons from the left side of the screen to the right side.\r\n\r\nWhen you've matched each icon with a letter, click the \"Check Answers\" button.\r\n\r\nThe letter will turn green if you get it correct.\r\n\r\nOnce all 4 are correct, you can continue.\r\n\r\nIf any are incorrect, you will not be able to get a green bubble on this level.",
    "preload_asset_list": null
  },
